---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

const meta = {
	description: "About Shameer Baramy. Backend, platform engineering, distributed systems, AI agents, and tools for thought.",
	title: "About",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
	<section>
		<h1 class="heading-1">About</h1>
		<div class="prose">
			<p>
				I'm Shameer, a backend and platform engineer.
			</p>
			<p>
				Most of my work has been on backend services, distributed systems, and
				the internal platforms and tooling that engineering teams run on. I
				write mostly Go and Python, with some TypeScript and Rust.
			</p>
			<p>
				The thread running through all of it is friction: the small frustrations
				that slow people down. A lot of what I do is figuring out how engineers
				and users can think and work better — better tools, better workflows,
				fewer things in the way. That's also what I tend to write about here:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Platform engineering and developer productivity</li>
				<li>LLM agents — building real software around models, not demos</li>
				<li>Distributed systems — Raft, replication, and how things fail in production</li>
				<li>Tools for thought and note-taking</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>
</PageLayout>
